---
# Project lint policy: keep the noise off, treat operational warnings
# (idempotency, risky shell patterns) as real findings.
#
# Background: var-naming generated ~95 warnings across the role tree —
# almost all of them false-positive complaints about register variables
# like `bw_session` not being prefixed with the role name. Refactoring
# every one of them gives zero operational benefit. The signal that
# matters (no-changed-when, risky-shell-pipe) was buried under that
# noise, so `just lint` exited non-zero and nobody noticed.

profile: basic

skip_list:
  # `bw_session` and similar legitimately cross role boundaries; the
  # role-prefix rule treats them as drift.
  - var-naming[no-role-prefix]
  # We use ignore_errors deliberately in a handful of places (the
  # zen_browser default-handler chain in particular). Demote to warn
  # instead of fail.
  - ignore-errors

warn_list:
  # FQCN for builtins is a style nit; surface but don't fail.
  - fqcn[canonical]
  # YAML cosmetic findings — surface but don't fail; real authoring
  # mistakes still get visibility from yamllint itself.
  - yaml[trailing-spaces]
  - yaml[line-length]
  - yaml[empty-lines]
  - yaml[commas]
  - key-order[task]
  # Surfaced but not blocking — we deliberately use systemctl/curl/shell
  # in a handful of bootstrap-y tasks where the systemd/get_url modules
  # don't offer enough control. Refactoring them is on the wishlist, not
  # a CI blocker.
  - command-instead-of-module
  - command-instead-of-shell
